On Monday, Azimio la Umoja presidential candidate Raila Odinga named Narc Kenya leader Martha Karua as his running mate. During the announcement, the former Prime Minister also laid out what his cabinet will look like if elected the fifth president of Kenya. In Raila's revealed lineup, Martha Karua will be the Deputy President and Justice and Constitutional Affairs Cabinet Secretary. Wiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka had been given the position of Chief Cabinet Secretary in the cabinet. He has, however, announced that he will be on the ballot as the One Kenya Alliance presidential candidate on August 9. Former National Assembly Speaker Kenneth Marende will be the Senate Speaker, while Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya will take the job of National Treasury CS. Peter Munya will retain his current slot as Agriculture CS but will have an additional role as Chairperson of the Kenya Productive Sector. Mombasa Governor Ali Hassan Joho will be the Lands Cabinet Secretary and among his responsibilities will be to fight historical land injustices at the Coast and across the country. Kalonzo has previously been Raila's running mate in the 2013 General election under Cord and in 2017 under the National Super Alliance.